wikipedia_page.main: John "Jackie" Arthur (14 December 1917 – 19 November 1986) was an English footballer.

response: * 19 November 1986 – Jackie Arthur, 68, played more than 200 games for Stockport County, Chester and Rochdale between 1938 and 1953 in a career which was disrupted by the war. He also had two spells with Everton but did not play a first team game for them.
